HEADWORD: Sonance
<hw>So"nance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sound;
a tune; <as>as, to sound the tucket <ex>sonance</ex></as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being sonant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sonant</ent>⟦br⟧
